Blackstar Network Ltd. (BSNK)

Transparency Semester Report 
January–June 2026

This transparency report summarizes notable milestones, infrastructure updates, and public project developments completed during the first half of 2026 by Blackstar Network Ltd. (BSNK).

Throughout January, development continued across internal infrastructure and public-facing projects. Efforts focused on expanding the BSNK tool suite, improving deployment workflows, and refining the organization's 
digital ecosystem in support of future services.

During February, the main domain blackstarnet.ltd was successfully renewed for another registration period. Several privately held domains within the BSNK portfolio were also renewed as part of ongoing infrastructure 
maintenance and long-term digital asset management.

On March 1st, Sky Archive (@skyarchiveair) officially launched on TikTok as a public web property operated by Blackstar Network Ltd. The project focuses on preserving aerial drone footage as a long-term digital archive. 
Later, on March 31st, Blackstar Network expanded its digital infrastructure through the acquisition of a blockchain domain, further strengthening its long-term digital presence.

Throughout April, work continued on improvements to Blackstar Network's backend infrastructure, internal systems, and development environment in preparation for future projects and services.

On the anniversary of Blackstar Network's formation in May 29th, the organization reached procurement-ready status for future contract work and hosting services.

On June 30th, Blackstar Network launched its official Blogspot publication as the organization's public announcements page for transparency reports, operational updates, and future notices.

During this reporting period, no BSNK projects, or hosted content were subject to legal takedown demands, compulsory disclosure orders, or requests from public or private sector institutions.

As always, Blackstar Network Ltd. remains committed to responsibly managing its digital infrastructure, and maintaining transparency regarding the organization's operations and significant developments.

Until the next report.
BSNK
